args: Ya been sayin' that for an hour,\njerkface! Now GET UP ALREADY!
Sorry, Princey! Just tryin' to get\nCaptain Idiot here outta bed.
Anyway, I'm gonna head into town.\nDon't keep me waitin'!
Are you sick, Yaten? You look unwell.
Just lemme sleep for a bit here.
(Wow, is he STILL not up? It's noon!)
(He used to leave the castle at the\ncrack of dawn, but lately he's been\nsleeping in more and more often.)
Uh oh, guys! We got a problem!
A huge argument just broke out between\nNatalie and the townspeople!
The little wing lady woke me with all her\ncaterwauling. Now come on. Let's go.
As if an outsider like you can\ndo anything to help our town!
A festival is the last thing we need!\nNow get out of here and leave us be!
Wouldja all shut up for a hot second\nand LISTEN TO ME ALREADY?!
Nothing you can say is worth hearing!\nHonestly, I have no idea what the mayor\nwas thinking when he brought you on.
Our first priority should be ensuring the\ntown is properly defended from fiends,\nnot THIS utter nonsense.
Oh, forget it. This town is a lost cause,\nand everyone here knows it!
Ah, hell. Now you're fightin' each OTHER?!
Everybody just slow your damn rolls\nfor a minute! Sheesh!
What are you all doing here?!
Standing around carping like this\nis just gonna tire everyone out.
So let's be adults and TALK.
And what would you have us ＂talk＂ about?!
How about the reason behind\nholding a festival?
I didn't suggest that your mayor hold\na festival without a reason, you know?
So look, protecting the town is important.\nNo one wants fiends attacking it again.
But! How are folks supposed to come\ntogether and protect it without unity?
Unless you lot think you're tough enough\nto go at everything alone?

Fortunately, the town's almost back to
normal, which means a festival is a
great chance to celebrate that AND
bring everyone together. You follow?

A good, cheery festival where everyone
speaks their minds is the perfect place
to put together plans to get this town
back on its feet again.
And look, as long as the prince is here,\nyou guys know you're safe—so why not\ngive this festival a chance?
Still, the thought of letting an outsider\norganize a festival for us is...
Well, THIS outsider's got it all covered.
Wait, is this the plan for the festival?
Ah! This is a list of our town's\ntraditional arts and crafts!
He's using them to decorate the town\nand the stalls. It's impressive work\nfor an outsider, I'll give him that.
Eh, you pick it up pretty quick if you just\nhang around and keep your ears open.
Wait a second. So you actually WERE\nworking this whole time?!
You weren't just eating and talking—\nyou were actually learning about this\ntown's customs and culture.
Hmm... It says here you're planning to use\ngold decorations on the floats?
That's one of your traditional designs,\nright? Seems perfect for a float.
It's a fine idea, but who will make it?\nAll of our artisans have already left.
All I did was copy other people's work.\nStill, I think it turned out all right.
I'm sorry, but you cannot simply pass off\nan imitation as the real thing. It is an\ninsult to both the town and our artisans.
...Which is why I will teach you\nto craft these items for REAL.
Ha! Sounds like there's at least one artisan\nwho stuck around! You're on, pal.
I can't stand around and do nothing when\nan outsider's doing this much to help us.
I agree. We at least owe it to you\nto see this festival out.
Well, that was a lot of effort,\nbut I'm glad it all worked out.
*yawn* Glad I didn't stay up\nmaking that for nothing.
Is that why you've been so tired lately?
I TOLD ya not to work nights, dummy!\nIt makes ya too tired to work in the DAY!
Anyway, if we're done here, I'm starving.
Ya better not stick the meal on\nsomeone else's tab this time!
I honestly can't tell if he's got it together\nor is actually a complete mess.
